# Code Review

When asked to review a PR, read and follow the code-review skill at `.cursor/skills/code-review/SKILL.md`.

The skill orchestrates a multi-agent PR review: gathers context (PR metadata, diff), triages changed files, dispatches 5 focused reviewer subagents in parallel, and consolidates findings into a unified report.

Reviewer subagents (`~/.cursor/agents/review-*.md`):

- `review-architecture` — correctness, SOLID, anti-patterns, code organization
- `review-react-typescript` — hooks, components, TypeScript strictness, a11y, i18n
- `review-security` — auth, injection, secrets, data exposure
- `review-performance` — complexity, rendering, memory, I/O
- `review-testing` — coverage gaps, test quality, determinism
